properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

  • Queensland, Heavy & Exempt vehicles should remain on the motorway
  • All other vehicles must exit onto the Gold Coast Hwy where there will be a police checkpoint

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

During peak travel periods, particularly weekday mornings, extensive delays may be experienced by motorists travelling into Queensland.

Visit qld.gov.au for more details.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND Cameron Corner Road
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Restrictions in effect include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

  • Light vehicles must obtain a pass for travel. Application for a pass can be found at https://www.qld.gov.au/border-pass
  • Once you obtain a pass call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 for code to gate.
  • Heavy vehicles do not require a pass. Call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 for code to gate.       
  • Thargomindah Police Station is to be contacted during business hours ONLY.
  • Please call prior to travel as you will not have phone service at the gate/border.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - ST PETERS Campbell Road on Campbell Rd Bridge
properties.otherAdvice:
Permanent traffic changes following the opening of Campbell Road bridge, St Peters from 5am Monday 22 June 2020

A number of permanent traffic changes will come into effect from 5am Monday 22 June, following the opening of the Campbell Road bridge. These changes are:
- Northbound traffic on Burrows Rd from Canal Rd must now turn left at Campbell Rd
- Southbound traffic on Burrows Road from Huntley Street must now turn left at Campbell Road onto the new Campbell Rd bridge towards Bourke Rd.
- Eastbound traffic on Campbell Rd can now turn left at Burrows Rd or continue eastbound towards Bourke Rd to travel across the new Campbell Rd bridge
- Northbound traffic on Bourke Rd from Gardeners Rd can now turn left onto the new Campbell Rd bridge to Campbell Rd or continue northbound on Bourke Rd .

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Bridge construction - MORORO TO CHATSWORTH ISLAND Pacific Hwy
properties.publicTransport:
Motorists are advised there will also be some changes to local bus stop pick up and drop off locations.  

  • The bus stop north of the old Mororo Bridge that was temporarily relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park will be reinstated to its original location.  
  • The school bus stop at Banana Road has been relocated to Woombah Woods Caravan Park bus stop on Iluka Road.   
  • The 386 service and school bus route will again access Chatsworth Road north via the old Mororo Bridge.
properties.otherAdvice:
There are changed traffic conditions on local roads for motorists connecting to the Pacific Highway between Mororo and Chatsworth Island. 

Motorists are advised to drive to the conditions, and follow the directions of signs and traffic control.
